1.SASS ?
It is a css preprocessor.
More work with less code and is more stable.
No of frameworks are built with sass.
Variables are created to store the information so that they can be used throughout the stylesheet.($ declaration)
Nesting is acheived with sass.
Two syntaxes 1-.scss  2-.sass

2.Advantages of sass ?
With less code more work is done.
Variables are declared and used to store information.
we can inherit the properties (extends)
nesting
mixins

3.SASS vs LESS vs STYLUS
SASS
-variables in sass start with $
-.sass extension
-nesting is allowed
LESS
-variables in sass start with @
-.less extension
-nesting is allowed
STYLUS
-no prefix
-.styl extension
-nesting is allowed